\ul POINT E\
\ulnone - The google map displaying the location of the city searched for has a custom marker\
- The marker is positioned at the location (Latitude, Longitude) of the location the weather has been requested for.\
- When the marker is clicked, an information window appears displaying a short summary (weather description, temperature and image) of the weather forecasted for the nearest time (ie. for the present day).\
- The information window can then be cleared be clicking the \'93x\'94 button.\
- At the same time that the info window is displayed for the marker a google line chart is displayed, showing a plot of the rainfall, temperature and windspeed for the number of days requested.\
- The chart can be removed again by clicking on the chart or by clicking on the marker on the map again.
